message.content: The likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are "cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.NE". The paper focuses on answering single-relation factoid questions over Freebase using a two-step pipeline of entity linking and fact selection. This task falls under the domains of natural language processing (NLP), artificial intelligence (AI), information retrieval (IR), machine learning (ML), and neural networks (NE), which are covered by the aforementioned sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in the sub-fields of computer vision (CV) and pattern recognition (PR), but the focus of the paper is on NLP and AI. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are those that cover NLP and AI, followed by IR, ML, and NE.
